{title: He Taught Me To Yodel}
{artist: Margo Smith}
{composer: Written by Tom Emerson, Paul Roberts, Esther Van Sciver}

[G]I climbed a big high mountain
On a clear and sunny day
[A7]There I met a yodeling guy
In a [D7]little Swiss chalet
[G]He taught me to yodel [C]yodel-oh-ee-dee
[D7]Diddly-odel-oh-ee-dee [G]diddly-odel-oh-ee-dee
He taught me to yodel [C]yodel-oh-ee-dee-ay-dee
[D7]Yodel-oh-ee-dee-yodel-oh-[G]dee
So now I wanna teach you
How to yodel just like me
[D7]It's easy when you're singing
To go yodel-diddly-oh-oh-dee
[G]First take a deep breath
Then you exhale one two three
[A7]Then you'll hear a yodel
If you [D7]listen close to me
[G]Yeah this is how to yodel [C]yodel-oh-ee-dee
[D7]Diddly-odel-oh-ee-dee [G]diddly-odel-oh-ee-dee
This is how to yodel [C]yodel-oh-ee-dee
[D7]Diddly-odel-oh-ee-dee-yodel-oh-[G]dee